  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally to examine the influence of blood viscosity and inlet flow-rate variation on the relative hemolysis index; results confirmed low parametric sensitivity across the five operating points evaluated, supporting the MRL 2 classification. No formal uncertainty quantification workflow was mandated at this risk level.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
